<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title><%= title %></title>
        <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    </head>
    <body bgcolor="#24273a" text="#cad3f5">

        <div class="center-content">
            
            <h1><%= title %></h1>
            <p>Welcome to my <%= title %> challenge</p>

            <hr />
            <center>

                <img src="/images/<%= title %>.png" alt="<%= title %>" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" />
            
                <p>During Module 4, I developed NOVA, an AI assistant designed to interact with external services. The original goal was to create a voice-controlled assistant while improving my software engineering skills through a larger software project.</p>
                <p>The project started with defining requirements and researching suitable frameworks and technologies. I then built a command-line interface prototype and gradually expanded its functionality through API integrations and additional features.</p>
                <p>The project resulted in a functional CLI-based assistant with multiple integrated features. Although voice control was part of the original plan, I was unable to complete it within the available time. This highlighted the importance of realistic planning and prioritising core functionality.</p>
            </center>
            
            <hr />
            <p><a href="https://kiliandiescher.org">Also check out my other projects on my portfolio!</a></p>
        
        </div>
    </body>
</html>